# System Patterns: Narva Website Architecture

## Design Patterns
- **Mobile-First Responsive**: Design for mobile, enhance for desktop
- **Grid-Based Layout**: CSS Grid for product showcases
- **Card Components**: Individual product cards with consistent structure
- **Hero Section**: Large banner with brand messaging
- **Navigation**: Sticky header with mobile hamburger menu

## Component Structure
```
├── Header Component
│   ├── Logo
│   ├── Navigation Menu
│   └── Mobile Menu Toggle
├── Hero Section
│   ├── Brand Tagline
│   ├── Featured Product
│   └── Call-to-Action
├── Product Grid
│   ├── Product Cards
│   │   ├── Product Image
│   │   ├── Product Name
│   │   ├── Fragrance Notes
│   │   └── Description
├── About Section
│   ├── Brand Story
│   └── Brand Values
├── FAQ Section
│   ├── Accordion Components
│   └── Question/Answer Pairs
└── Footer Component
    ├── Contact Information
    ├── Social Links
    └── Copyright
```

## Styling Approach
- **CSS Variables**: Define brand colors and typography
- **BEM Methodology**: Block-Element-Modifier naming
- **Utility Classes**: Reusable spacing and typography
- **Component Isolation**: Self-contained component styles

## Brand Identity Integration
- **Color Palette**: Extracted from logo and product images
- **Typography**: Luxury-focused font selections
- **Imagery**: Consistent product photography style
- **Spacing**: Generous whitespace for premium feel

## Responsive Breakpoints
```css
/* Mobile First */
.container { /* Base mobile styles */ }

/* Tablet */
@media (min-width: 768px) { /* Tablet styles */ }

/* Desktop */
@media (min-width: 1024px) { /* Desktop styles */ }

/* Large Desktop */
@media (min-width: 1440px) { /* Large screen styles */ }
```

## JavaScript Patterns
- **Progressive Enhancement**: Core functionality without JS
- **Event Delegation**: Efficient event handling
- **Module Pattern**: Organized, reusable JS components
- **Mobile Interactions**: Touch-friendly interactions